properties.abstract: The rocky head sitting on the grassy cone-shaped mountain is an inviting view, even from afar. Tierhöri can be reached within only a few hours. The ascent is mainly easy, but on the summit structure the hike turns into a truly alpine endeavour. You need the help of your hands, and being sure-footed, unafraid of heights and experienced in scrambling is required. Chindbettihore is a neighbouring summit which can be included in this tour.
properties.subtitle: Short tour to an original summit
properties.title: From Engstligenalp via Chindbettipass

sac_photos.title: Tierhöri viewed from the south-east (from Rote Totz)
Below the couloirs on the south-east side of Tierhöri
On the ascent from Chindbettipass to Tierhöri. On the left-hand side is Chindbettihorn, below on the right Tälliseeli.

segments.description: Hike on a marked mountain hiking trail from the summit station of the aerial cableway to the chalet at 1963 m on the eastern border of Engstligenalp. Follow the signposts Chindbettipass from the beginning, even though the trail makes a little detour. Engstligenalp is an alpine alluvial plain protected by the law and listed as a wetland of national importance. Therefore please do not walk on unmarked paths. The entire mountain hiking trail is marked from the chalet to Chindbettipass.
segments.title: Engstligenalp – Chindbettipass

segments.description: On Chindbettipass leave the trail and ascend southward on the ridge towards Tierhöri. At first the area with boulders is somewhat labyrinthine, but further on you will find faint paths and some cairns. At ca. 2780 m, where the rocks raise vertically, there is a steep scree slope leading up between the rocks, after that it is less steep until right before the summit head. On a faint path go round the rocks to the right. From the west you can now scramble up a couloir between the two rocky pinnacles and then to the left up to the summit (I). Early or late in the year this couloir may be filled with snow or ice. In this case continue on a faint path round the summit head to the southern side of the mountain. From there, also in gullies and couloirs, climb up to the summit. On this side the difficulty is slightly higher (II), in exchange, the passage is warm and sunny. Descend back to Chindbettipass on the same route.

photos.caption: On the ascent from Chindbettipass to Tierhöri. On the left-hand side is Chindbettihorn, below on the right Tälliseeli.
Below the couloirs on the south-east side of Tierhöri
The main summit of Tierhöri can be reached climbing easily on the rocks on the right.

segments.title: Chindbettipass – Tierhöri – Chindbettipass

segments.description: Instead of directly descending from Chindbettipass to Engstligenalp, it is worthwile to hike westward round Chindbettihorn on the marked mountain hiking trail and then on Entschligegrat with its splendid panorama to Tschingellochtighore. Go left, pass below the bizarre towers of Tschingellochtighore and descend on Ärtelegrat to Engstligenalp.
segments.title: Chindbettipass – Ärtelegrat – Engstligenalp

segments.description: Lovely alternative descent: from Entschligegrat between Chindbettihore and Tschingellochtighore descend east on a marked mountain hiking trail to Tälli and on to Waldiswang. Continue east below the impressive Schwarzgrätli to P. 2381, then descend to Berghotel Schwarenbach and on a wide walking trail to Sunnbüel (aerial cableway and bus to Kandersteg station). Entschligegrat–Sunnbüel ca. 2 h, T3–.
segments.title: Alternative descent Entschligegrat – Sunnbüel
